  "answer": "## Answer\nAutonomous agents are best when the problem is open-ended and the model needs to choose tools, adapt mid-flight, and recover from wrong turns. Workflow-based agents are best when the task is well-defined and you want tighter control, clearer inspection, and more repeatable execution. In short: more autonomy buys flexibility, but usually at the cost of more latency, cost, and variance; more workflow structure reduces flexibility, but improves controllability, observability, reproducibility, and failure recovery. `https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/building-effective-agents` `https://openai.com/business/guides-and-resources/a-practical-guide-to-building-ai-agents/` ([anthropic.com](https://www.anthropic.com/research/building-effective-agents/))\n\n### Required aspect coverage\n- Flexibility: autonomous agents fit ambiguous work that needs model-driven adaptation; workflows fit well-defined tasks. `https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/building-effective-agents` ([anthropic.com](https://www.anthropic.com/research/building-effective-agents/))\n- Controllability: workflows use predefined code paths, typed edges, and versioned snapshots; autonomous agents decide their own tool use within guardrails. `https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/agent-builder` `https://openai.com/business/guides-and-resources/a-practical-guide-to-building-ai-agents/` ([anthropic.com](https://www.anthropic.com/research/building-effective-agents/))\n- Observability: OpenAI explicitly adds observability tools plus trace graders, and notes that production agents previously lacked sufficient visibility. `https://openai.com/index/new-tools-for-building-agents/` `https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/agent-builder` ([openai.com](https://openai.com/index/new-tools-for-building-agents/))\n- Cost: Anthropic says agentic systems often trade latency and cost for better task performance. `https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/building-effective-agents` ([anthropic.com](https://www.anthropic.com/research/building-effective-agents/))\n- Reproducibility: workflow versioning, preview/debug, and durable execution make outcomes more repeatable than fully autonomous loops. `https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/agent-builder` `https://openai.com/index/equip-responses-api-computer-environment/` `https://docs.temporal.io/` ([platform.openai.com](https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/agent-builder))\n- Failure recovery: agents can halt and hand control back to the user, but workflow engines like Temporal can resume after crashes, network failures, or outages. `https://openai.com/business/guides-and-resources/a-practical-guide-to-building-ai-agents/` `https://docs.temporal.io/` `https://openai.com/index/inside-our-in-house-data-agent/` ([openai.com](https://openai.com/business/guides-and-resources/a-practical-guide-to-building-ai-agents/))\n\n## Sources\n- Anthropic — Building Effective AI Agents `https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/building-effective-agents` ([anthropic.com](https://www.anthropic.com/research/building-effective-agents/))\n- OpenAI — A practical guide to building agents `https://openai.com/business/guides-and-resources/a-practical-guide-to-building-ai-agents/` ([openai.com](https://openai.com/business/guides-and-resources/a-practical-guide-to-building-ai-agents/))\n- OpenAI — New tools for building agents `https://openai.com/index/new-tools-for-building-agents/` ([openai.com](https://openai.com/index/new-tools-for-building-agents/))\n- OpenAI — Agent Builder docs `https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/agent-builder` ([platform.openai.com](https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/agent-builder))\n- OpenAI — Inside OpenAI’s in-house data agent `https://openai.com/index/inside-our-in-house-data-agent/` ([openai.com](https://openai.com/index/inside-our-in-house-data-agent/))\n- Temporal Docs homepage `https://docs.temporal.io/` ([docs.temporal.io](https://docs.temporal.io/))\n\n## Limitations\nThe evidence 